definition.value: Catalysis of the conversion of a di- or tetrachlorinated dienol to the corresponding catechol.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2,5-dichloro-2,5-cyclohexadiene-1,4-diol + NAD+ -eq- NADH + H+ + 2,5-dichlorohydroquinone.
Catalysis of the reaction -  trans-1,2-dihydrodiolphenanthrene + NAD+ -eq- H+ + NADH + 1,2-dihydroxyphenanthrene.
Catalysis of the reaction -  cis-1,2-dihydrobenzene-1,2-diol + NAD+ -eq- catechol + NADH + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  cis-1,2-dihydronaphthalene-1,2-diol + NAD+ -eq- naphthalene-1,2-diol + NADH + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  3-oxoadipate + NAD(P)+ -eq- 2-maleylacetate + NAD(P)H + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  (3S,4R)-3,4-dihydrophenanthrene-3,4-diol + NAD(+) -eq- H(+) + NADH + phenanthrene-3,4-diol.
Catalysis of the reaction -  cis-1,2-dihydroxycyclohexa-3,5-diene-1-carboxylate + NAD+ -eq- catechol + CO2 + NADH + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  cis-3-phenylcyclohexa-3,5-diene-1,2-diol + NAD+ -eq- biphenyl-2,3-diol + NADH + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  dihydrophloroglucinol + NADP(+) -eq- H(+) + NADPH + phloroglucinol.
Catalysis of the reaction -  cis-2,3-dihydroxy-2,3-dihydro-p-cumate + NAD(+) -eq- 2,3-dihydroxy-p-cumate + H(+) + NADH.
Catalysis of the reaction -  cis-1,2-dihydroxy-1,2-dihydrodibenzothiophene + NAD(+) -eq- 1,2-dihydroxydibenzothiophene + H(+) + NADH.
Catalysis of the reaction -  NAD(+) + pimelyl-CoA -eq- 2,3-didehydropimeloyl-CoA + H(+) + NADH.
Catalysis of the reaction -  4-chlorobenzoyl-CoA + chloride + NADP(+) -eq- 2,4-dichlorobenzoyl-CoA + NADPH.
Catalysis of the reaction -  cis-4,5-dihydroxycyclohexa-2,6-diene-1,2-dicarboxylate + NAD(+) -eq- 4,5-dihydroxyphthalate + H(+) + NADH.
Catalysis of the reaction -  5,6-dihydroxy-3-methyl-5,6-dihydroquinolin-2(1H)-one + NAD(+) -eq- 5,6-dihydroxy-3-methyl-2-oxo-1,2-dihydroquinoline + H(+) + NADH.
Catalysis of the reaction -  cis-1,2-dihydro-3-ethylcatechol + NAD(+) -eq- 3-ethylcatechol + H(+) + NADH.
Catalysis of the reaction -  cis-1,2-dihydroxy-4-methylcyclohexa-3,5-diene-1-carboxylate + NADP+ -eq- 4-methylcatechol + NADPH + H+ + CO2.
Catalysis of the reaction -  1,6-dihydroxy-2-methylcyclohexa-2,4-dienecarboxylate + NAD(+) -eq- 3-methylcatechol + CO(2) + NADH.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2 ADP + cyclohexa-1,5-diene-1-carbonyl-CoA + oxidized ferredoxin + 2 phosphate -eq- 2 ATP + 2 H(2)O + benzoyl-CoA + reduced ferredoxin.
Catalysis of the reaction -  quinoline + acceptor + H2O -eq- isoquinolin-1(2H)-one + reduced acceptor.
Catalysis of the reaction -  acetophenone + CO2 -eq- H+ + benzoyl acetate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  benzoyl-CoA + oxidized ferredoxin + H2O -eq- 4-hydroxybenzoyl-CoA + reduced ferredoxin.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2-aminobenzoyl-CoA + 2 H+ + 2 e- -eq- NH3 + benzoyl-CoA.
Catalysis of the reaction -  cyclohexylamine + O2 + H2O -eq- cyclohexanone + NH3 + hydrogen peroxide.
Catalysis of the reaction -  iminodiacetate + OH- -eq- H+ + 2 e- + glyoxylate + glycine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  nitrilotriacetate + NADH + H+ + O2 -eq- NAD+ + H2O + glyoxylate + iminodiacetate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  (R)-6-hydroxynicotine + H(2)O + O(2) -eq- 6-hydroxypseudooxynicotine + H(2)O(2).
Catalysis of the reaction -  (S)-6-hydroxynicotine + H(2)O + O(2) -eq- 6-hydroxypseudooxynicotine + H(2)O(2).
Catalysis of the reaction -  N5,N10-methenyltetrahydromethanopterin + H2 -eq- N5,N10-methylenetetrahydromethanopterin.
Catalysis of the reaction -  nitrilotriacetate + OH- -eq- H+ + 2 e- + glyoxylate + iminodiacetate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  nicotine + acceptor + H2O -eq- (S)-6-hydroxynicotine + reduced acceptor.
Catalysis of the reaction -  5-methyltetrahydromethanopterin + coenzyme F420 + H(+) -eq- 5,10-methylenetetrahydromethanopterin + reduced coenzyme F420.

Catalysis of the generic reaction -  epoxide + CO2 + NAD+ + electron donor -eq- beta-keto acid + NADH + reduced electron donor -  the electron donor may be NADPH or a dithiol. This reaction is the ring opening and carboxylation of an epoxide -  for example -  epoxypropane + CO2 + NAD+ + NADPH -eq- acetoacetate + NADH + NADP+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  1,4-benzoquinone + H(+) + NADPH -eq- hydroquinone + NADP(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  2,3-dihydroxy DDT + O2 -eq- 6-oxo-2-hydroxy-7-(4-chlorophenyl)-3,8,8,8-tetrachloroocta-2E,4E-dienoate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  4-amino-2-hydroxylamino-6-nitrotoluene + NADP+ -eq- NADPH + H+ + 4-amino-2-nitroso-6-nitrotoluene.
Catalysis of the reaction -  4-carboxy-4'-sulfoazobenzene + 4 H+ + 4 e- -eq- 4-aminobenzoate + 4-aminobenzenesulfonate.
Catalysis of the conversion of a nitrate group to an amino or hydroxylamino group on toluene or a toluene derivative.
Catalysis of the reaction -  nitrobenzene + 2 NADPH + 2 H+ -eq- hydroxyaminobenzene + 2 NADP+ + H2O.
Catalysis of the removal of one or more nitrite (NO2-) groups from nitroglycerin or a derivative.
Catalysis of the reaction -  pentaerythritol trinitrate + NADPH -eq- NADP+ + nitrate + pentaerythritol dinitrate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  methanethiol + O2 + H2O -eq- formaldehyde + hydrogen sulfide + hydrogen peroxide.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2,3,5,6-tetrachlorohydroquinone + 2 glutathione -eq- 2,3,6-trichlorohydroquinone + glutathione disulfide + HCl.
Catalysis of the reaction -  trithionate + acceptor + 2 H2O + OH- -eq- 3 HSO3- + reduced acceptor.
Catalysis of the reaction -  3-(2,3-dihydroxyphenyl)propionate + O2 -eq- 2-hydroxy-6-keto-nona-2,4-dienedioate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  1,2-dihydroxynaphthalene + O2 -eq- 2-hydroxychromene-2-carboxylate. C6 of the substrate molecular may have an NH2 group attached.
Catalysis of the reaction -  phenanthrene + NADH + H+ + O2 -eq- NAD+ + cis-3,4-dihydroxy-3,4-dihydrophenanthrene.

Catalysis of the reaction -  2,3-dihydroxybenzenoid + O2 -eq- H+ + distal extradiol ring cleavage. Substrates are 2,2',3-trihydroxybiphenyl (forms 2-hydroxy-6-oxo-6-(2-hydroxyphenyl)-hexa-2,4-dienoate) and 2,2',3-trihydroxydiphenylether (forms 2,3-hydroxy-6-oxo-6-(2-hydroxyphenyl)-hexa-2,4-dienoate).
Catalysis of the reaction -  1,2-dihydroxyfluorene + O2 -eq- 2-hydroxy-4-(2-oxo-1,3-dihydro-2H-inden-1-ylidene) but-2-enoic acid.
